Restore drill: restore a point from the target's destination into a scratch root, open it, and scan every key. Proves the backup restores end to end

Usage: sleet mirror drill [OPTIONS] <ROOT> <DB> <TARGET>

Arguments:
  <ROOT>
          Fleet root URL, e.g. s3://ops/sleet/

  <DB>
          Registered database URL

  <TARGET>
          Mirror target name

Options:
      --at <AT>
          The restore point: a manifest id or an RFC 3339 timestamp. Default: the backup's latest manifest

      --scratch <SCRATCH>
          Empty scratch root URL to restore into. Default: a fresh local temp directory

      --keep
          Keep the scratch root instead of removing it

      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format

          Possible values:
          - text: Human-readable text
          - json: JSON matching the subcommand's response schema
          
          [default: text]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
